    q: "Do you service the rotisserie motor on Twin Eagles and Viking outdoor grills?",
    a: "Yes. Rotisserie motors fail in two patterns. The first is gear-drive seizure from grease ingress — the motor housing on Twin Eagles TEBQ36R and TEBQ54R, on Viking VGBQ-series, and on the Wolf Outdoor OG units sits directly above the rotisserie burner where airborne grease aerosol settles into the housing over 8 to 10 years. The motor stops mid-cook or refuses to start cold. Replacement runs $220 to $380 for the motor and labor. The second pattern is brush wear on units that get heavy use — country-club-style entertainers on Trousdale who run the rotisserie weekly will see brush wear at the 5 to 7 year mark, manifesting as the motor turning under no load but stalling under a 12-pound prime rib. We carry the most common rotisserie motors (Twin Eagles, Viking, Lynx, Alfresco) on the truck."
  },
