<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 — About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Beverly Hills outdoor entertaining runs on built-in luxury grills — and we keep them running.</h2>

    <p>Outdoor entertaining is structural to how Beverly Hills households use their homes. The estates we service in Trousdale, the Flats, Holmby Hills, and the Beverly Hills Post Office area are designed around outdoor kitchens that anchor pool decks, terraces, and rear gardens. The grill at the center of those kitchens is rarely a freestanding cart — it's a built-in luxury unit dropped into a stone or stucco enclosure, integrated with side burners, warming drawers, outdoor refrigeration, and often a power burner or pizza oven. When that grill goes down before a Friday evening or a Sunday brunch, the household needs it back online today, not next week.</p>

    <p>The luxury BBQ market in Beverly Hills concentrates around a specific group of brands. Lynx Professional Series — including the L54PSR with rotisserie and the Asado plancha cooktop — leads the calendar in Trousdale and the higher-end estate rebuilds. Alfresco ALXE shows up across the Flats and BH Post Office area. Twin Eagles TEBQ36R and TEBQ54R appear in the country-club-adjacent installations and the Holmby Hills estates. Viking Outdoor (VGBQ series), Wolf Outdoor (OG series), DCS by Fisher &amp; Paykel, Hestan, and Fire Magic Aurora round out the mix. The infrared specialists — TEC Sterling FR, TEC Patio FR, and Solaire — show up most often in the homes where the chef or homeowner is serious about searing. We're factory-trained on all of these, and we carry the most-needed igniters, burners, valves, and rotisserie motors on the truck.</p>

    <p>This page is for built-in luxury BBQ specifically. If you have a freestanding cart-style grill — Weber, Char-Broil, mid-tier Napoleon — see <a href="/services/bbq-grill-repair/">BBQ grill repair</a>, our general hub. If your outdoor kitchen also includes a refrigerator, ice maker, or wine cooler that's down, the relevant service hubs cover those: <a href="/services/outdoor-refrigerator-repair/">outdoor refrigerator repair</a> and <a href="/services/wine-cooler-repair/">wine cooler repair</a>. The point of this page is the grill at the center of your Beverly Hills outdoor kitchen — and the fastest way to get it back online.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02 — The failure tree</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built-in BBQ failures we see in Beverly Hills.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Luxury built-in BBQ grills fail along a predictable failure tree. We work the cheap and common items first, then escalate. Roughly 80% of Beverly Hills calls resolve in the first three failure modes below; the rest are gas-train or infrared-specific repairs that need brand-specific expertise.</p>

    <div class="failure-grid">
      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>1. Igniter failure (most common)</h3>
        <p>Single most common no-light call we run in BH. Lynx uses the Quikliter spark module; Alfresco runs an integrated piezo-and-spark assembly; Twin Eagles uses flame-thrower modules; Wolf and Viking use battery-powered hot-surface igniter packs. The failure pattern is consistent across brands — moisture migrates into the igniter compartment over 4 to 7 years, corrodes the electrode, the spark gap, or the wire harness, and the burner stops lighting reliably. We test with a meter before quoting parts. About a quarter of igniter calls resolve at the electrode-cleaning stage with no part replacement; the rest need a module swap. Truck-stocked across the brands above.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>2. Burner corrosion or blockage</h3>
        <p>Stainless burners on Lynx Trident, Alfresco ALXE, Twin Eagles, and Viking last 6 to 10 years before tube corrosion at the venturi end starts producing uneven flame patterns or yellow tipping. Symptoms: one burner runs colder than the others, flame pattern is uneven across the tube, or you see soot accumulating on the cooking grates above one zone. We pull the burner, inspect the tube and venturi, clear spider blockages (a real cause on outdoor grills that haven't been used through the winter), and replace the tube if the corrosion has gone past the point of cleaning. OEM-only on luxury builds — generic substitutes hot-spot and void warranty.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>3. Gas valve stuck open or closed</h3>
        <p>The brass control valves on luxury built-ins are over-engineered but they do fail — typically the valve stem seizes from carbon build-up at the orifice end, or the spring-loaded safety mechanism on a Viking or Wolf valve gets gummed up from grease infiltration. Symptoms: the knob turns but the burner doesn't respond, or worse, the valve stays partially open even when the knob is in the off position (a safety issue). We pressure-test the manifold, identify the failed valve, and replace as a unit. Lynx, Alfresco, Twin Eagles, Viking, Wolf, and DCS all use brand-specific valve geometries; OEM only.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>4. Temperature inconsistency (thermometer + valve combo)</h3>
        <p>"The grill won't hold temperature" is a diagnostic that combines two separate failures: the cabinet thermometer reading drifting (mechanical or digital probe) and the valve flow becoming non-linear (carbon-fouled orifice). We diagnose both. About 60% of "temperature problem" calls in BH trace to a fouled or failed thermometer probe — the actual cooking temperature is fine, the gauge is wrong. The other 40% is a valve flow issue that requires manifold work. We don't replace expensive parts based on the gauge alone — we put a calibrated probe in the cabinet to verify the actual temperature first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>5. Rotisserie motor</h3>
        <p>Rotisserie motors on Twin Eagles, Lynx, Alfresco, Viking, and Wolf live directly above the rotisserie burner where grease aerosol settles into the gear housing over 8 to 10 years. Two failure modes: gear-drive seizure (motor doesn't spin under any load) and brush wear (motor spins under no load but stalls under a 10-pound prime rib). We test under load before quoting. Replacement is the most common path — most rotisserie motors aren't economically rebuildable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>6. Infrared burner failure (TEC, Solaire — specialty)</h3>
        <p>TEC Sterling FR, TEC Patio FR, Solaire, and Lynx ProSear infrared burners use a ceramic radiant tile that pressurizes during operation. When you hear a popping or swooshing sound, or the heat output drops noticeably, the ceramic has cracked. There is no field repair — these burners are sealed assemblies that get replaced as units. TEC and Solaire share a common Sterling-pattern burner family (SOL-TEC-STBAS) that we carry on the truck. Lynx ProSear is a different geometry, OEM-only. Replacement runs $380 to $680. Honest diagnostic: if the tile is cracked, replacement is the only path; we don't pretend otherwise.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>7. Grease management blockage</h3>
        <p>Built-in grills generate significant grease, and they're designed with a slide-out drip tray and a grease drain that channels rendered fat into a collection cup or a sealed disposal pan. When the drip tray slides seize, the drain holes clog, or the drain channel rusts through (more common on units 12+ years old), grease accumulates inside the cabinet base where it becomes a fire risk and an odor source. We see this most often on grills that haven't had a service-and-clean in 3+ years. Full service-and-clean — degreasing the cabinet, clearing the drain, lubricating slides, inspecting all gas connections — is a defined service we run for $320 to $520.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="failure-card">
        <h3>8. Regulator and gas-train</h3>
        <p>Less common but more important. The regulator on a built-in BBQ controls gas pressure from the supply (natural gas line or LPG tank) to the manifold. A failing regulator produces low flame across all burners simultaneously — a pattern that's diagnostically distinct from a single-burner valve issue. We pressure-test the manifold with a manometer to verify regulator output is within spec. On natural-gas hard-piped builds in Beverly Hills (almost all of them), regulator replacement is straightforward; we coordinate with the household's gas service if a shutoff valve isn't accessible.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03 — Brands and models</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BBQ &amp; grill brands we service in Beverly Hills.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Luxury built-in BBQ in Beverly Hills concentrates around ten brands. Each has a different parts chain and a different characteristic failure mode.</p>

    <div class="brand-grid">
      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Lynx (most common)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">L54PSR · L42 · L36 · Asado plancha · Sedona · ProSear infrared</p>
        <p>The dominant built-in luxury grill in Beverly Hills. Quikliter igniter modules, Trident burner system, ProSear infrared rotisserie burner. Common items: igniter modules at 5 to 8 years, Trident burners at 7 to 10 years, ProSear ceramic at 6 to 10 years. Truck-stocked on the most-needed parts; less common items 1 to 3 day lead through authorized distribution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Alfresco</h3>
        <p class="model-list">ALXE-30 · ALXE-36 · ALXE-42 · ALXE-56 · AGBQ Sear Zone</p>
        <p>Alfresco ALXE is a major share of the BH Flats and renovation-kitchen calendar. Integrated piezo-and-spark igniter system, Sear Zone infrared on the larger units, robust 304 stainless cabinet. Common service: igniter assembly, Sear Zone burner replacement, gas valve replacement. Alfresco parts chain is generally good — most components stocked in regional distribution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Twin Eagles</h3>
        <p class="model-list">TEBQ36R · TEBQ54R · Eagle One · 36" / 42" / 54" built-in</p>
        <p>Twin Eagles concentrates in country-club-adjacent installs and the Holmby Hills estates. Heavy 304 stainless construction, flame-thrower igniters, robust rotisserie motors. The cabinet and burner system both hold up well past the 10-year mark. Common service items: rotisserie motor at year 8 to 10, igniter modules at year 6 to 8, occasional gas valve work. Parts through Twin Eagles authorized distribution; we carry the most common items truck-stocked.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Viking Outdoor</h3>
        <p class="model-list">VGBQ-series · VGIQ built-in · 30" / 36" / 41" / 53"</p>
        <p>Viking VGBQ is moderate-frequency in our BH calendar — concentrated in renovations from 2008 to 2018. 304 stainless cabinet, hot-surface igniter packs, robust valve manifold. Common service: igniter pack replacement, burner tube replacement, rotisserie motor at year 8 to 10. Viking parts chain is reasonably fast — most components 1 to 2 day lead through Middleby distribution (Viking's parent company).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Wolf Outdoor</h3>
        <p class="model-list">OG30 · OG36 · OG42 · OG54 · Outdoor Gas Grill</p>
        <p>Wolf Outdoor is concentrated in higher-end Westside renovations. Flame Tamer burner system, integrated rotisserie infrared on the OG36 and larger, Wolf-pattern igniter assemblies. Common service: igniter at year 5 to 7, infrared rotisserie burner at year 7 to 10, rotisserie motor at year 8 to 10. Sub-Zero / Wolf parts chain is quick through authorized distribution; we have current ordering relationships.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>TEC Sterling and Patio FR (infrared specialty)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">Sterling FR · Sterling II · Sterling III · Patio FR · Patio II · G-Series</p>
        <p>TEC is the original infrared grill — every burner is a ceramic radiant tile. We stock the SOL-TEC-STBAS family burner on the truck because it's the single most-replaced infrared burner in the LA luxury market. Tile cracking at year 6 to 10 is the dominant failure; symptoms are the popping/swooshing sound and dropping heat output. Replacement runs $380 to $680. Cabinet and gas-train hold up well past 15 years.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Solaire (infrared specialist)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">36 IRBQ · 42 IRBQ · 56 IRBQ · Anywhere Portable</p>
        <p>Solaire's infrared cooking surface is the focal point of the product. All-stainless cabinet, brand-specific infrared burner architecture (compatible with TEC Sterling-pattern in some models). Common service: infrared burner replacement at year 6 to 10, igniter at year 5 to 8. Solaire's parts chain is direct from the manufacturer; lead time is 2 to 4 days when not truck-stocked.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Fire Magic</h3>
        <p class="model-list">Aurora A430 · A540 · A660 · A790 · Echelon Diamond E660 · E790</p>
        <p>Fire Magic Aurora is mid-frequency in BH — typically appears in builder-spec outdoor kitchens from 2012 onward. Diamond Sear cooking grids, Hot Surface igniter, robust burner system. Common service: igniter, burner replacement, gas valve work. Fire Magic parts chain is one of the better-stocked among the luxury brands.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>DCS by Fisher &amp; Paykel</h3>
        <p class="model-list">DCS Series 9 · Series 7 · 36" / 48" built-in</p>
        <p>DCS shares parts platforms with Fisher &amp; Paykel commercial. Sealed grease management, U-shaped burners, integrated rotisserie. Common service: rotisserie motor, U-burner replacement, igniter module. Parts come through F&amp;P authorized distribution; lead time generally 2 to 4 days on uncommon parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="brand-card">
        <h3>Hestan</h3>
        <p class="model-list">GMBR36 · GMBR42 · GSBR · Aspire</p>
        <p>Hestan is concentrated in newer Westside renovations from 2018 onward. Marquise stainless, Trellis burner system, Sear-on-Demand infrared rotisserie. Premium build quality with parts available through Hestan authorized distribution. We have current ordering relationships; common parts arrive within 2 to 4 business days.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 WHAT MAKES BH DIFFERENT -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 — How Beverly Hills service is different</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What makes Beverly Hills BBQ service different.</h2>

    <p>Beverly Hills households operate on a different schedule than the rest of our service area. The grill is rarely the homeowner's direct concern — the call comes from the estate manager, the household chef, or the property manager who runs the residence. The diagnostic conversation starts with "we have 18 for dinner Saturday and the rotisserie won't turn" rather than "my BBQ is broken." We're used to that. Our dispatcher routes Beverly Hills event-prep calls to the front of the queue when the household tells us there's a hard deadline.</p>

    <p>Pool-house and pavilion BBQ setups are common in Trousdale and Holmby Hills — secondary outdoor kitchens that get heavy weekend use during entertaining season and lighter use through the winter. We service these on the same call as the main outdoor kitchen when the household asks; one truck visit, both setups inspected and repaired. Our techs are factory-trained on the brands listed above and we don't substitute generic parts on luxury builds without your explicit approval.</p>

    <p>Discretion matters in Beverly Hills. We arrive in low-profile vehicles when the home requests it, work directly with the estate manager or chef without disturbing the household, and clear the work area completely before we leave. Estate managers and household chefs in Trousdale, the Flats, Holmby Hills, and the BH Post Office area know us by name; we've been on these properties for years. Same-day service is standard; written estimates before any parts are quoted; OEM parts on luxury builds.</p>
